**Category:** essay-draft sartre other-minds being-and-nothingness morris mcculloch shame look

**Abstract:**
Major essay dated August 10, 1998 titled "Sartre on the existence of others" responding to Katherine Morris's article in Sartre Studies International. Critiques both Morris's defense of Sartre and McCulloch's analytic critique. Examines Sartre's argument that shame before the Other yields certainty of the Other's existence as subject. Questions whether Sartre's distinction between Other-as-subject and Other-as-object results in a viable alternative to solipsism or a "ghostly, eyeless Other."

**AI Recommendation:** Major essay on Sartre's epistemology of Other minds.

